esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when Kubernetes nodes report not ready status.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Node status ready=false — node offline, unable to accept workloads.
//
// What it means:
// Node failed health checks — existing pods may be evicted.
//
// Common causes:
// Kubelet crash, network issues, resource exhaustion, container runtime failure.
//
// Action needed:
// Check node logs, kubelet status, system resources, and network connectivity.
//
// To scope to a cluster, add: AND `orchestrator.cluster.name` == "YOUR_CLUSTER"
TS metrics-kubernetes.node-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.node.status.ready` == "false"
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.node.name`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
